1. Generalization¶

1.1 Best Pre-forming Model¶

This was the model that was recorded during the process of Grid Search, the best preforming model uses the optimizer Adamax and has a learning rate of 0.01 which had a recorded accuracy of 78% which was 2% higher then using the optimizer Adam.

1.1.1 Import the Required Libraries¶

In [48]:
import tensorflow as tf
import numpy as np
import matplotlib
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, Dropout, Activation, Flatten, Conv2D, MaxPooling2D, AveragePooling2D, GaussianNoise
from tensorflow.python.keras.optimizers import Adamax
import pickle

%matplotlib inline

1.1.2 Load in the Data¶

In [2]:
X = pickle.load(open("X.pickle","rb"))
y = pickle.load(open("y.pickle","rb"))

1.1.3 Set the Random Seed¶

In [3]:
np.random.seed(1)

1.1.4 Normalize the Data¶

In [4]:
X = X/255.0

1.1.5 Create the Model¶

In [50]:
model = Sequential()

model.add(Conv2D(16, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', input_shape = X.shape[1:]))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))

model.add(Conv2D(32, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal'))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
          
model.add(Conv2D(64, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal'))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))

model.add(Conv2D(128, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal'))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))

model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal'))
model.add(Activation("relu"))

model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal'))
model.add(Activation("relu"))

model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal'))
model.add(Activation("relu"))

model.add(Dense(1))
model.add(Activation("sigmoid"))

optimizer = Adamax(lr=0.01)

model.compile(loss="binary_crossentropy",
             optimizer=optimizer,
             metrics=['accuracy'])

model = Sequential()

model.add(Conv2D(16, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', input_shape = X.shape[1:]))

model = Sequential()

model.add(Conv2D(16, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', input_shape = X.shape[1:]))

1.3 Bias¶

1.3.1 Convolutional Layer¶

1.3.1.1 Create the Model¶

In [178]:
model = Sequential()

model.add(Conv2D(16, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True, input_shape = X.shape[1:]))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

model.add(Conv2D(32, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))
          
model.add(Conv2D(64, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

model.add(Conv2D(128, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal'))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(Dropout(0.1))

model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal'))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(Dropout(0.1))

model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal'))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(Dropout(0.1))

model.add(Dense(1))
model.add(Activation("sigmoid"))

optimizer = Adamax(lr=0.01)

model.compile(loss="binary_crossentropy",
             optimizer=optimizer,
             metrics=['accuracy'])

1.3.3 Both Convolution & Dense Layers¶

1.3.3.1 Create the Model¶

In [196]:
model = Sequential()

model.add(Conv2D(16, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True, input_shape = X.shape[1:]))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

model.add(Conv2D(32, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))
          
model.add(Conv2D(64, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

model.add(Conv2D(128, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(Dropout(0.1))

model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(Dropout(0.1))

model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(Dropout(0.1))

model.add(Dense(1))
model.add(Activation("sigmoid"))

optimizer = Adamax(lr=0.01)

model.compile(loss="binary_crossentropy",
             optimizer=optimizer,
             metrics=['accuracy'])

model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))
          
model.add(Conv2D(64, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

model.add(Conv2D(128, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(GaussianNoise(0.4))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(Dropout(0.1))

model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(GaussianNoise(0.4))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(Dropout(0.1))

model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(GaussianNoise(0.4))
model.add(Dropout(0.1))

model.add(Dense(1))
model.add(Activation("sigmoid"))

optimizer = Adamax(lr=0.01)

model.compile(loss="binary_crossentropy",
             optimizer=optimizer,
             metrics=['accuracy'])

1.5 Image Augmentation¶

Image Augmentation allows the dataset to increase by modifying the existing images by using a zoom, a skew, random distortions etc to increase the size of the dataset without having to collect more unique data. To preform this task I decided to use the Augmentor Python library. The library uses a Pipe-line which is connected to the original source directory of images. Augmentor has their output directory hardcoded to create a new directory known simply as output in the original categories folder. To manage this I manually moved the newly created images to a new folder which would hold all the outputted images. This was preformed on both the Categories in the dataset and the newly created data was brought into one folder.

1.5.1 Create the Augmented Images - Healthy¶

1.5.1.1 Create the Augmentor¶

In [219]:
import Augmentor
p = Augmentor.Pipeline("DATA/Healthy")

Initialised with 250 image(s) found.
Output directory set to DATA/Healthy\output.

1.5.1.2 Initialise the Modifications¶

In [220]:
p.zoom(probability=0.4, min_factor=1.1, max_factor=1.5)
p.skew(probability=0.2)
p.random_distortion(probability=0.2, grid_width=6, grid_height=6, magnitude=16)
p.rotate(probability=0.4, max_left_rotation=10, max_right_rotation=10)
p.shear(probability=0.2, max_shear_left=6, max_shear_right=6)
p.flip_random(probability=0.4)
p.skew_tilt(probability=0.4)

1.5.1.3 Augment the Data-set¶

1500 images were created. Instead of adding an extreme value for this parameter a small value such as 1500 ensures that the modifications will not create distorted images which would serve no overall use to the training of this model.

1.5.3.3 Create the Training Set¶

In [228]:
training_data = []

def create_training_data():
    for category in CATEGORIES:
        path = os.path.join(DATADIR, category)
        class_num = CATEGORIES.index(category)
        for img in os.listdir(path):
            try:
                img_array = cv2.imread(os.path.join(path, img), cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
                blur = cv2.GaussianBlur(img_array,(5,5),0)
                new_array = cv2.resize(blur, (IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE))
                training_data.append([new_array, class_num])
            except Exception as e:
                pass
            
create_training_data()

1.5.5.1 Create the Model¶

In [257]:
model = Sequential()

model.add(Conv2D(16, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True, input_shape = X.shape[1:]))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

model.add(Conv2D(32, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))
          
model.add(Conv2D(64, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

model.add(Conv2D(128, (3,3), dilation_rate=2, strides=1, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), padding="same"))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(64, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(GaussianNoise(0.2))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(Dropout(0.1))

model.add(Dense(64, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(GaussianNoise(0.2))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(Dropout(0.1))

model.add(Dense(64, kernel_initializer='normal', use_bias=True))
model.add(GaussianNoise(0.2))
model.add(Activation("relu"))
model.add(Dropout(0.1))

model.add(Dense(1))
model.add(Activation("sigmoid"))

optimizer = Adamax(lr=0.01)

model.compile(loss="binary_crossentropy",
             optimizer=optimizer,
             metrics=['accuracy'])
